<h2>Anti-Abuse Policy</h2>

<p>
  It is our intention that [% terms.Bugzilla %] remains a useful tool for reporting 
  and commenting on [% terms.bugs %], feature requests, and tasks for the Mozilla community.
</p>

<p>
  In order to keep [% terms.Bugzilla %] a useful, inclusive place for this work, we have 
  <a href="page.cgi?id=etiquette.html">[% terms.Bugzilla %] Etiquette</a> 
  for using this site which, by using this site, you agree to follow.
</p>

<p>
  If you find a [% terms.Bugzilla %] user violating or <a href="page.cgi?id=etiquette.html">[% terms.Bugzilla %] Etiquette</a> 
  or the <a href="https://www.mozilla.org/about/governance/policies/participation/">Mozilla Community Participation Guidelines</a> 
  in comments on [% terms.bugs %], please <a href="https://wiki.mozilla.org/BMO/comment_tagging">tag the comments</a> 
  in question so that an administrator can review them. 
<p>

<p>
  If you need to contact a [% terms.Bugzilla %] community administrator urgently, 
  please use the #bmo channel on irc.mozilla.org or email 
  <a href="mailto:bugzilla-admin@mozilla.org">bugzilla-admin@mozilla.org</a> with
  the [% terms.bug %] number and a short description of the situation.
</p>

<p>
  If a comment is abusive or threatening use the tag <b><i>admin</i></b>. An admin will 
  receive a notification shortly and be able to follow up. [% terms.Bugs %] with 
  comments marked, 'abuse', 'spam', and 'advocacy' will also be reviewed.
</p>

<p>
  If a [% terms.bug %]'s short-description, whiteboard tags, attachments, 
  or other user-created content violate Mozilla Community Participation 
  Guidlines or [% terms.Bugzilla %] Etiquette, please describe the issue 
  in a comment and tag that comment <b><i>admin</i></b>.
</p>

<p>
  If the content of a user's name field contains abusive or offensive content,
  contact an administrator at 
  <a href="mailto:bugzilla-admin@mozilla.org">bugzilla-admin@mozilla.org</a> 
  or the #bmo channel on irc.mozilla.org.
</p>

<p>
  <b>If another [% terms.Bugzilla %] user asks you to stop a behavior that violates [% terms.Bugzilla %] Etiquette or the Mozilla Community Participation Guidelines, stop doing it.</b>
</p>
 
<p>
  <b>If an administrator asks you to stop a behavior, stop doing it.</b> 
</p>

</p>
  Administrators have the discretion to limit or suspend your account,
  and take further actions if necessary.
</p>

<p>
  Questions about this policy should be addressed to 
  <a href="mailto:bugzilla-admin@mozilla.org">bugzilla-admin@mozilla.org</a>.
</p>

